    b = t.count('2')
    c = t.count('3')
    if b + c != n: return -1
    d = t.count('4')
    if d > b: return -1
    f = t.count('6')
    if f < c: return -1
    return '1 2 4\n' * d + '1 3 6\n' * c + '1 2 6\n' * (n - d - c)

def main(n, nums):
	ex = n//3
	if 5 in nums or 7 in nums or nums.count(1)!=ex:
		return -1
	else:
		s = ''
		q = nums.count(4)
		w = nums.count(6)
		e = nums.count(3)
		r = nums.count(2)
		if r!=q+w-e or w!=e+r-q or e>w or q>r:
			return -1
		s+='1 2 4\n'*q
		s+='1 2 6\n'*(ex-q-e)
		s+='1 3 6\n'*e
		return s[:-1]
